place.name: SOUTH LYNN
place.gazetteerText: LYNN (SOUTH), a parish in Lynn district, Norfolk; forming part of Lynn borough. Real property, £14,601; of which £1,060 are in gas-works. Pop. in 1851,4,772; in 1861,4,534. Houses, 1,031. The living is a vicarage in the diocese of Norwich. Value, £403.* Patron, the Bishop of Norwich. See LYNN. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
